	<description>	
		Orange Helicopter is a one-man games studio, founded by former game AI researcher Ed Powley, and based in York, UK.
	</description>
		
	<histories>
		<history>
			<header>Early history</header>
			<text>
				Many games companies have been founded by university dropouts.
				I decided to go a less conventional route: I graduated, got a PhD and spent several years working as a researcher before dropping out.
				My research was on artificial intelligence for board and card games.
				As well as publishing a number of &lt;a href="http://scholar.google.co.uk/citations?user=ERihGdQAAAAJ"&gt;journal and conference articles&lt;/a&gt;,
				my work found its way into the popular Android game &lt;a href="https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=uk.co.aifactory.spadesfree"&gt;Spades Free&lt;/a&gt; by AI Factory.
				However I eventually decided that making games from start to finish might be more fun than just making AI.
			</text>
		</history>
		<history>
			<header>Now</header>
			<text>
				Orange Helicopter's first title will be Blobjam, a physics-based action puzzle game.
			</text>
		</history>
		<history>
			<header>The name</header>
			<text>
				I read somewhere that (random colour) + (random object) was a good way to come up with a memorable company name.
				Orange Helicopter was the first combination I tried where the .com domain was available.
				(Note to self: need to ret-con a more interesting origin story for the name.)
			</text>
		</history>
	</histories>
	
